The High Court in Pietermaritzburg has dismissed, with costs, an application brought by late King Goodwill Zwelithini's first wife. Queen Sibongile Dlamini-Zulu applied to inherit 50% of the late King’s estate on the basis that she’s the first wife. Siphamandla Goge and Lethiwe Mdluli have more #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403  PIETERMARITZBURG - The execution of the late King Goodwill Zwelithini's will has been suspended, for now. Judge Isaac Madondo has ruled that its validity will have to be ascertained during a trial. READ: WATCH: Judgment on the validity of King Zwelithini's will This application was brought forward by two princesses from the Amazulu Royal House. At the same time, an application brought by Queen Sibongile Dlamini-Zulu claiming 50% of the late King Goodwill Zwelithini’s estate has been dismissed with costs. Watch the video above for more details on this story. The execution of late King Goodwill Zwelithini's will has been suspended for now. Judge Isaac Madondo has ruled that its validity will have to be ascertained during a trial. This application was brought forward by two princesses from the Amazulu Royal House.